{
  "texts": [
    "Steps (1), (2), (3) and (6) were all performed via individual model inferences given different prompts, and step (5) was performed via one model inference per document.",
    "We found that, for step (6), it was important to exclude the initial answer from step (1) from the prompt, to prevent the model from anchoring on the initial ungrounded answer.",
    "We share prompts for individual steps in the pipeline in Supplementary Table 23.",
    "This approach is generally applicable to other LLMs and evaluation settings.",
    "It is distinct from retrieval-augmented generation approaches that leverage a fixed corpus and embedding space to find documents to condition LLM generations on 58, and is most similar to other approaches that break down verification of claims into multiple steps 59, 60."
  ]
}